.TH "arm_iommu_create_mapping" 9 "arm_iommu_create_mapping" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
arm_iommu_create_mapping \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct dma_iommu_mapping *" arm_iommu_create_mapping
.BI "(struct bus_type *bus "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t base "  ","
.BI "u64 size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bus" 12
pointer to the bus holding the client device (for IOMMU calls)
.IP "base" 12
start address of the valid IO address space
.IP "size" 12
maximum size of the valid IO address space
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Creates a mapping structure which holds information about used/unused
IO address ranges, which is required to perform memory allocation and
mapping with IOMMU aware functions.

The client device need to be attached to the mapping with
arm_iommu_attach_device function.
